        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 17 at 4:49PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 449 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Peyton, or 22 miles northeast of Colorado Springs, moving east at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Calhan and Peyton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM MDT for
east central Colorado.</instruction>
